The paper deals with the problem of downlink beamformer design for signal-to-interference-plus-noise ratio balancing in a multiuser multicell environment with imperfectly estimated channels at base stations. This problem is related to several areas of computer science, including information theory (cs.IT), networking and internet architecture (cs.NI), systems and control (cs.SY), multimedia (cs.MM), and machine learning (cs.LG). However, given the focus on optimization and signal processing techniques, we believe that cs.IT and cs.NI are the most likely categories, followed by cs.SY, cs.MM, and cs.LG.
